rComments: Prof. Franks is a clear lecturer. Nice British accent. The material was very interesting and insightful, though at times it was a bit confusing. The powerpoints he used were somewhat distracting. Available for help during office hours, but was really not that helpful in the end because he never answered my questions fully.

For a second year course the material is barely comprehensible and the expectations are ridiculous. I am a 4.0 student and have never been so lost in a course. Don't get me wrong, he is a smart guy and knows what he is talking about but the density of the material and how fast he moves through it is ridiculous.
Prof. Franks is a good professor. He is clear and concise, though the material itself can be difficult at times. He keeps the class fairly engaged. Assignments and grading are done fairly.
